The formula for calculating Net Positive Suction Head Available is simple.
NPSHA = H_absolute + H_static - H_friction - H_vaporization
where H_absolute represents the absolute pressure exerted on the fluid column, H_static represents the pressure at the base of the fluid column due to the height
of fluid, H_friction is the pressure loss due to frictional losses in the piping system, and H_vapor is the vapor pressure of the fluid, all expressed in meters of
water.

The frictional losses term can be calculated using the Hagen-Pouiselle equation assuming that the fluid is in laminar flow and flowing through a vertical length
of piping. 

